wikipedia_page.main: Leslie Francis Howe (3 March 1912 – 23 February 1999) was an English professional footballer who played for Enfield, Northfleet United and Tottenham Hotspur and represented England at schoolboy level.

response: *Les Howe (1912–1999), professional footballer with 165 appearances for Tottenham Hotspur was born in Bengeo.
*23 February 1999: Les Howe, 86, scored 26 league goals in 165 appearances for Tottenham Hotspur as a wing-half in the 1930s before his career was effectively ended by the war.
